    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.22-23_0001a" />
                <note type="curatorial">173-2               Aly Collection</note>
             
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                Skyrim, Route 7,<lb/>
                Columbia, Mo.<lb/>
                
                Aug. 25, 62
                    </dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I've thought often of you since my return home, and especially of our evening of comradeship. That sort of thing does not happen often to either of us, but during a long life I've had a few glorious times with friends whom I respected and admired and who respected me. I 
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.22-23_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    think of such comrades with a peculiarly warm affection and a sense of obligation &#8212; and you are one of them.</p>
                
                <p>You said several things that I recall clearly and with gratefulness. For instance, you quoted your Lucile as saying that I'm a good man. That is something to remember, and I do want it to be true. Also, you made me feel that you care for me. 
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.22-23_0002a"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                    
                    As a matter of fact, you said as much, and I returned the compliment heartily.</p>
                
                <p><del>Po</del>More power to you, Comrade &#8212; and many thanks for your goodness to this old man.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                
                <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
